Sentencas: A two-dimensional isothermal mathematical model is developed for an anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell using samaria doped-ceria as electrolyte.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C

Sentencas: This model takes into account species transfer and electrochemical reaction processes for cell operating between 500 degrees C and 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C

Sentencas: In this model, it is assumed that the electrochemical reactions take place not only at the electrolyte/electrode boundaries, but also throughout the electrodes.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C

Sentencas: The model is validated with the experimental data.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C

Sentencas: The geometry and operating parametric analyses are conducted to understand the coupled electrochemical reaction and species transfer phenomena.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C

Sentencas: The results indicate that the rate of leakage current increases with the increase either in cell operating voltages, or in cell operating temperatures.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C

Sentencas: It is also found that higher hydrogen concentration in the fuel stream results in larger leakage current.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C

Sentencas: Further, the current efficiency decreases with the increase either in cell active areas, or in cell operating temperatures.
Titulo: Modeling of anode-supported SOFCs with samaria doped-ceria electrolytes operating at 500-600 °C
